Ringier to Expand TV Business, Handelsblatt Reports

-- B y   A l l i s o n   C o n n o l l y
-- 
2011-03-15T06:41:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/ringier-plans-to-expand-tv-business-walder-tells-handelsblatt.html
(Corrects name of television station in second, third
paragraphs.)  Ringier AG wants to expand its
television business, possibly through the acquisition of a TV
station,  Handelsblatt  reported, citing Marc Walder, head of the
Swiss media company’s business in Switzerland and  Germany .  The company is in good financial shape and acquisitions
would be decided on whether they are a good fit for the company,
Walder told the newspaper.  Ringier could be targeting 3+, Handelsblatt said, citing
unidentified people in the industry.  The Swiss station hasn’t been in talks with or received an
offer from Zurich-based Ringier, 3+ Chief Executive Dominik
Kaiser told the newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Allison Connolly in  Frankfurt  at 
 aconnolly4@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at   pserafino@bloomberg.net . 